title: How did you mastered the art of programming?
text:
Who qualify to be a master programming?

Anyone who can create websites, games, from scratch with their own brain and google help without following tutorials line by line.

So, how did you mastered the art of programming? If it was practice, what did you practice?

I was talking to a guy and he said to me that he has finished a DSA book thrice(fcking thrice) and solved same 500 problems thrice. That's how he mastered programming.

What's your secret sauce?

Show HN: Nino Drive – Block-based file storage module
text:
Hi, we're releasing 2 new modules on Nino:

Nino Drive works exactly like how you imagine it to be and is interoperable with the rest of Nino. Bonus: every download link is valid up to 5 minutes only; your files stay secure and private when you no longer share them.

Nino Collection is a folder-like utility module. It works like a folder but can contain not just documents and files but also any module such as Nino Todo or Nino Blog, hence the name. Any module under a collection will inherit its permission settings.

They are the 4th and 5th modules released on Nino, a modular workspace app.

Previously:

- Nino Doc https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=34451023

- Nino Todo https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=34608404

- Nino Blog https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=34749522
